column5: Thanks and I hit a record, only 74 pounds total
Rich,won't be long now and your fillet knife will be bloody.Stay warm up there at good ole Hornby lake.
Had a pike left in freezer from last couple of days of ice fishing and figured I better use it up.Great tasting fish.https://youtu.be/V290lIZFM9k
After I watched that vid,I went my freezer to see if I had a northern,notta one,I'll have to do something about that soon.
I knew I had them.Havnt been in freezer all that long.Great tasting fish.Freezer cleaned out know so will be only fresh fish for rest of season.
They don't taste very good when I'm trying to eat it through my iPad.
On cedar Monday! Fish dinner Monday night!
Wish I was sitting at your dinner table Monday!hope you get some eyes.
My favorite and you got me hungry. Leaving today for Red Lake and can’t wait!!!!!!!!!
Good luck. Weather will be much better this week.
Saw the post title, thot it was about pike tiny ones (fry), rather than cooking some up. Pics looked appetizing! Bill
